/**
 * HUBSPOT ↔ GOOGLE SHEETS ↔ MAILUP: EVENT-DRIVEN INTELLIGENCE ENGINE
 * Version: 7.1 — Enterprise Hardened (Concurrency + Persistence Safe)
 *
 * ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
 * WHAT'S NEW IN v7.1 vs v7.0  (Enterprise Hardening Phase)
 * ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
 *
 * ✅ FIX A — Mutex Locking (LockService) — Race Condition Prevention
 *    → doPost()             — serialises concurrent webhook deliveries
 *    → upsertContactRow()   — prevents simultaneous writes to the same row
 *    → syncMailUpToSheets() — prevents back-sync collision with live webhooks
 *    → syncSheetsToHubSpot()— prevents write-back collision with back-sync
 *    → All locks use 10-second waitLock with guaranteed releaseLock in finally{}
 *    → doPost returns HTTP 503 (retry) when lock cannot be acquired in time
 *
 * ✅ FIX B — Circular Buffer for PROCESSED_EVENT_IDS — Persistence Safety
 *    → Previous cap: 5000 IDs → up to 95 KB → CRASHES PropertiesService (9 KB limit)
 *    → Audit suggested cap: 1000 IDs → still 19 KB → STILL CRASHES
 *    → Correct safe cap: 400 IDs → 7.6 KB → 20% headroom below 9 KB limit
 *    → Calculation: 400 × (16-digit ID = 19 bytes in JSON) = 7,600 bytes < 9,216 bytes
 *    → Circular: oldest IDs dropped first as new ones arrive; dedup window = 400 events
 *
 * ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
 * WHAT'S NEW IN v7.0 vs v6.7
 * ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
 *
 * ✅ HubSpot Webhook Receiver (doPost)
 *    → Real-time contact.creation / contact.propertyChange / contact.deletion
 *    → Webhook signature verification (HMAC-SHA256)
 *    → Idempotent event processing (dedup by eventId)
 *
 * ✅ Full Event-Driven Contact Sync
 *    → handleContactCreate   — fetches & upserts row on HubSpot creation event
 *    → handleContactUpdate   — patches only the changed field on property change
 *    → handleContactDelete   — soft-deletes row (status → "Deleted")
 *
 * ✅ MailUp → Sheets Back-Sync  (syncMailUpToSheets)
 *    → Pulls unsubscribes, bounces, spam complaints from MailUp
 *    → Updates corresponding Sheets rows (Status, Message)
 *
 * ✅ Sheets → HubSpot Write-Back  (syncSheetsToHubSpot)
 *    → Propagates MailUp outcomes (unsubscribed, bounced) back to HubSpot
 *    → Updates hs_lead_status and hs_email_optout on matching contacts
 *
 * ✅ Full Reconciliation Mode  (fullReconciliation)
 *    → Diffs HubSpot contacts ↔ Sheets ↔ MailUp
 *    → Repairs missing, stale, or orphaned records in all three platforms
 *
 * ✅ Auto Webhook Registration  (registerHubSpotWebhooks)
 *    → One-click setup: registers contact.creation / propertyChange / deletion
 *    → Reads Web App URL from script properties
 *
 * ✅ Time Trigger Setup  (setupTimeTriggers)
 *    → Installs scheduled GAS triggers for back-sync & reconciliation
 *
 * ✅ HubSpot Contact ID tracking  (Column 18)
 *    → Stored on every row for precise update matching without email lookups
 *
 * ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
 * PRESERVED FROM v6.7
 * ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
 * ✅ Industry-Sorted Ingestion
 * ✅ Industry-Sequential MailUp Push
 * ✅ Signal Aggregation (UPSERT)
 * ✅ AI Inference on Aggregates
 * ✅ AI Segmentation (word-boundary fix)
 * ✅ Gap Detection
 * ✅ Dead Letter Queue
 * ✅ Retry Failed Pushes
 * ✅ All v6.x security fixes (#11 #12 #13)
 */

